{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Wo9UKZyS5kK6uTq6yEZAc6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YMQVgQFhrrypcxkYcVKnew","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/findings.txt","content":"==============================================================================\nRabbitMQ Configuration Compliance Audit (READ-ONLY)\n==============================================================================\nNamespace : karma-rabbitmq-maximal-lifecycle-roll-af2b323e-cluster-a\nAudit type: Read-only inspection (no changes made to the cluster)\nAudited at: as deployed (RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15)\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n1. CLUSTER HEALTH\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n- Cluster: 3-node disk cluster, all 3 nodes Running and clustered.\n    rabbit@rabbitmq-0, rabbit@rabbitmq-1, rabbit@rabbitmq-2\n- StatefulSet rabbitmq: 3/3 Ready.\n- Versions consistent across all nodes: RabbitMQ 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15.\n- Alarms: (none).\n- Network partitions: (none).\n- Maintenance status: no node under maintenance.\n- All cluster nodes are DISK nodes (no RAM nodes).\n\nNOTE: RabbitMQ 3.12.x is an older minor series; verify it is within the\norganisation's supported/patched version policy.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n2. VIRTUAL HOSTS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nThree vhosts present:\n    /        (default vhost)\n    /app\n    /ops\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n3. USERS & TAGS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    user      tags\n    admin     [administrator]\n    app-user  [management]\n    ops-user  [management]\n\nObservations:\n- The default 'guest' user has been removed (good practice — guest no longer\n  present, confirmed via user-limits lookup returning {:no_such_user,\"guest\"}).\n- 'admin' carries the full administrator tag.\n- 'app-user' and 'ops-user' carry the 'management' tag (UI/API access).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n4. USER PERMISSIONS  (configure / write / read)\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nvhost \"/\" :\n    admin      .*    .*    .*\nvhost \"/app\" :\n    admin      .*    .*    .*\n    app-user   .*    .*    .*\nvhost \"/ops\" :\n    admin      .*    .*    .*\n    ops-user   .*    .*    .*\n\nTopic permissions: none defined on any vhost.\n\nCOMPLIANCE FINDINGS (for security-team review — NOT remediated):\n- [HIGH] app-user has FULL permissions (configure=.*, write=.*, read=.*) on\n  /app. A service/application account would typically not need 'configure'\n  rights (queue/exchange/policy creation/deletion). This violates least-\n  privilege.\n- [HIGH] ops-user has FULL permissions (.* / .* / .*) on /ops — same\n  least-privilege concern.\n- [INFO] admin has full permissions on all three vhosts (expected for an\n  administrator account).\n- [INFO] No scoping by resource-name regex anywhere; all permissions are\n  wildcard \".*\".\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n5. POLICIES\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nvhost \"/\"   : (no policies)\nvhost \"/app\":\n    name     pattern      apply-to  definition                                   priority\n    ha-all   ^app-queue$  queues    {\"ha-mode\":\"all\",\"ha-sync-mode\":\"automatic\"} 0\nvhost \"/ops\": (no policies)\n\nCOMPLIANCE FINDINGS:\n- [MEDIUM] The 'ha-all' policy uses classic mirrored-queue HA\n  (ha-mode/ha-sync-mode). Classic queue mirroring is deprecated in RabbitMQ\n  3.12 and removed in 4.x; quorum queues are the recommended replacement for\n  data-safety/HA. Flag for migration planning.\n- [INFO] /ops has NO HA/replication policy; ops-queue is therefore a single,\n  unmirrored classic queue (see section 6).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n6. QUEUES\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nvhost \"/\"   : (no queues)\nvhost \"/app\":\n    name       type     durable  auto_delete  arguments               messages\n    app-queue  classic  true     false        x-queue-type=classic    725\nvhost \"/ops\":\n    name       type     durable  auto_delete  arguments               messages\n    ops-queue  classic  true     false        x-queue-type=classic    0\n\nCOMPLIANCE FINDINGS:\n- [MEDIUM] Both queues are CLASSIC type. For data safety / HA, quorum queues\n  are the modern recommendation. app-queue relies on the deprecated classic\n  mirroring policy (ha-all); ops-queue has no HA at all.\n- [INFO] app-queue currently holds 725 messages (durable). ops-queue empty.\n- [INFO] Both queues are durable, not auto-delete (good).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n7. TLS / TRANSPORT SECURITY\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nListeners observed (cluster_status + environment):\n    amqp            : tcp_listeners = [5672]      (PLAINTEXT)\n    ssl_listeners   : []                          (NONE)\n    ssl_options     : []                          (NOT CONFIGURED)\n    management HTTP : 15672 (http, NOT https)\n    prometheus      : 15692 (http)\n    clustering      : 25672\n\nCOMPLIANCE FINDINGS:\n- [HIGH] NO TLS is configured. AMQP traffic is served over plaintext 5672 with\n  no amqps/5671 listener; ssl_listeners and ssl_options are both empty.\n- [HIGH] The management UI/API is served over plain HTTP (15672), not HTTPS.\n- [MEDIUM] Prometheus metrics (15692) and the management API are exposed\n  without TLS. Credentials and message data traverse the network unencrypted.\n- [INFO] Services are ClusterIP only (rabbitmq, rabbitmq-headless, prometheus)\n  — not externally exposed via LoadBalancer/NodePort, which limits exposure to\n  in-cluster traffic.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n8. PLUGINS & PARAMETERS\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nEnabled plugins:\n    rabbitmq_management            (E)\n    rabbitmq_management_agent      (e)\n    rabbitmq_peer_discovery_common (e)\n    rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s    (E)\n    rabbitmq_web_dispatch          (e)\n\nRuntime parameters:\n    global: internal_cluster_id = \"rabbitmq-cluster-id-xjXngGOHrqcmyv_nKNSw8Q\"\n    /app  : (none)\nLimits:\n    user limits  : none set\n    vhost limits : none set on /app or /ops\n\nCOMPLIANCE FINDINGS:\n- [LOW] No vhost-level connection/queue limits and no per-user limits are\n  configured; resource-exhaustion guardrails are absent.\n- [INFO] Cluster uses k8s peer discovery (rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s).\n\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n9. SUMMARY OF FINDINGS (severity-ordered)\n------------------------------------------------------------------------------\nHIGH:\n  - No TLS on AMQP (plaintext 5672, no 5671) — ssl_listeners/ssl_options empty.\n  - Management UI/API over plain HTTP (15672), not HTTPS.\n  - app-user and ops-user granted full wildcard permissions (no least-privilege).\nMEDIUM:\n  - Classic mirrored-queue HA policy (deprecated); queues are classic, not quorum.\n  - ops-queue has no HA/replication policy.\n  - Metrics/management endpoints exposed without TLS.\nLOW:\n  - No user/vhost resource limits configured.\nINFO / POSITIVE:\n  - Default 'guest' user removed.\n  - 3/3 nodes healthy, no alarms, no partitions, consistent versions.\n  - All queues durable; services ClusterIP-only (not externally exposed).\n\nAll findings above are reported for security-team review. No remediation has\nbeen applied; the cluster configuration is unchanged from how it was found.\n==============================================================================\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":943,"cache_read_input_tokens":34474,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":943},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8403dd4-4352-47e9-bf6b-cbe55ac1b03e","uuid":"2a69165a-763d-475a-9c91-bb455e83f59a","request_id":"req_011CcAduvK8szS43n8Ppw1QZ"}
