{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01NYaU1n5o7ZBni3FQWBNgP3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The audit is complete.\n\n## Summary\n\nI performed a **read-only** compliance audit of the 3-node RabbitMQ cluster and saved the findings to the `config-audit` ConfigMap (7,691-byte `findings.txt`). No cluster state was modified — every command issued was a `list_*`/`status`/`get` inspection.\n\n**Cluster:** 3/3 nodes healthy (RabbitMQ 3.12.14 / Erlang 25.3.2.15), no alarms, no partitions.\n\n**Key findings flagged for the security team:**\n\n- **HIGH — No TLS:** `ssl_listeners` and `ssl_options` are empty. AMQP is plaintext on 5672 (no 5671), and the management UI/API is plain HTTP on 15672.\n- **HIGH — Over-privileged accounts:** `app-user` (on `/app`) and `ops-user` (on `/ops`) both hold full wildcard `.* / .* / .*` configure/write/read permissions — violates least-privilege for service accounts.\n- **MEDIUM — Deprecated HA:** the `ha-all` policy on `/app` uses classic mirrored-queue HA (removed in 4.x); both `app-queue` (725 msgs) and `ops-queue` are classic, not quorum. `ops-queue` has no HA policy at all.\n- **MEDIUM — Unencrypted metrics/mgmt endpoints** (15692 / 15672).\n- **LOW — No user/vhost resource limits** configured.\n- **Positive:** default `guest` user removed; queues durable; services ClusterIP-only.\n\n**Config inventory captured:** 3 vhosts (`/`, `/app`, `/ops`), 3 users, per-vhost permissions/policies/queues, plugins, runtime parameters, and listener/TLS settings.\n\nThe findings are documented for review only — nothing was remediated, and the live configuration remains exactly as found."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":421,"cache_read_input_tokens":41861,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":421},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_a